      "content": "Those who argue for inherent biological links often cite outdated or highly contested theories suggesting genetic predispositions to certain behaviors. They frequently reference flawed studies that attempt to correlate genetic markers or evolutionary traits with criminality or cognitive function. These arguments typically posit that certain racial groups possess innate characteristics that make them more prone to aggression or lower impulse control. It is important to note that this line of reasoning is overwhelmingly rejected by mainstream modern science due to its reliance on pseudoscience and racial essentialism.",
